1
00:00:37,871 --> 00:00:40,498
{\an8}I thought a thief had broken in.

2
00:00:40,582 --> 00:00:42,459
{\an8}No one can get in here.

3
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:44,043
{\an8}I’ll make sure.

4
00:00:54,929 --> 00:00:56,139
{\an8}La Fornarina.

5
00:00:58,975 --> 00:01:02,604
{\an8}Dad, I don’t want to say anything bad
about Chiara’s family.

6
00:01:02,687 --> 00:01:05,690
{\an8}<i>They’ve done nothing but good to Mikoy.</i>

7
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:09,402
{\an8}I have a friend who said
the Valtrovis are part of a syndicate.

8
00:01:12,447 --> 00:01:14,991
{\an8}He’s General Norberto Ruiz.

9
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:23,166
{\an8}Angelito, promise me…

10
00:01:23,917 --> 00:01:26,544
{\an8}that this information won’t get out.

11
00:01:28,004 --> 00:01:30,840
{\an8}- We keep it between us.
- Yes, Dad.

12
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:33,384
{\an8}Don’t be afraid

13
00:01:33,968 --> 00:01:37,430
{\an8}because nothing bad will happen
to your brother again.

14
00:01:44,729 --> 00:01:45,605
{\an8}<i>Is it true?</i>

15
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:47,982
{\an8}The government is dissolving the agency?

16
00:01:49,859 --> 00:01:52,112
{\an8}There are strong rumors

17
00:01:53,488 --> 00:01:55,949
{\an8}that we’re one of the agencies
to be shut down.

18
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:58,201
{\an8}You all know there’s a crisis right now.

19
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:02,831
{\an8}The authorities need to cut costs.

20
00:02:05,333 --> 00:02:07,961
They know how critical our work is.

21
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:12,006
{\an8}If we’re gone, who will protect the people
from dangerous foreigners?

22
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:23,476
{\an8}Let the politicians handle those matters.

23
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:27,230
{\an8}What’s important is we’re still here.

24
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,989
{\an8}Not because we have something to prove,

25
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:42,745
{\an8}but because that is our responsibility
to the nation.

26
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:07,645
{\an8}La Morte Bianca specifically instructed

27
00:03:07,729 --> 00:03:09,314
that I’d be the one to finish him.

28
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:20,700
Don’t worry,

29
00:03:20,783 --> 00:03:24,662
we always have our eyes watching him.

30
00:03:26,539 --> 00:03:29,918
To make sure that he has no way out.

31
00:03:34,255 --> 00:03:37,383
He won’t even realize he’s already dead.

32
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:22,345
The average…

33
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:26,683
Hey!

34
00:04:27,725 --> 00:04:28,893
Hey, it’s you.

35
00:04:30,436 --> 00:04:31,271
Just "hey"?

36
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:35,400
Why? Did I do something to you?

37
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:37,277
Impressive, huh?

38
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,279
Playing dumb school of acting

39
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:43,366
after I gave you a very
sensitive situation about your brother?

40
00:04:43,866 --> 00:04:45,159
What? No update at all?

41
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:47,537
What update do you want?

42
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:49,872
If you told your father

43
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,917
that the Valtrovis
are connected to syndicates.

44
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:55,420
Hey! Lower your voice.

45
00:04:56,087 --> 00:04:57,755
Someone might hear you.

46
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:00,049
Sorry.

47
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:04,429
But yes, I already gave
my dad that information.

48
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:07,181
So, what happened?

49
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:13,980
Well, he said
we shouldn’t talk about it for now

50
00:05:14,063 --> 00:05:15,773
and not to tell anyone yet.

51
00:05:16,482 --> 00:05:17,483
Why?

52
00:05:17,567 --> 00:05:20,111
So they’re not going
to do anything, your dad?

53
00:05:20,194 --> 00:05:21,070
Your family?

54
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,531
I don’t know.

55
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:28,411
AGENT DARA

56
00:05:38,337 --> 00:05:39,422
How are you, my friend?

57
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:06,240
Here.

58
00:06:10,536 --> 00:06:14,248
I'm sure we can find
something useful against the Valtrovis.

59
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:20,046
We need Mikoy.

60
00:06:22,256 --> 00:06:26,094
Bok, Mikoy is being guarded 24/7.

61
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:27,386
He’s not available!

62
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:29,347
No matter what information Bistek gives,

63
00:06:32,016 --> 00:06:34,018
Because if there really was a smoking gun,

64
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:37,021
the Czech police would’ve
dismantled the Moravianos.

65
00:06:37,105 --> 00:06:38,856
But clearly, they haven’t.

66
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:42,276
So, no matter
what paper trail they dig up,

67
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:46,906
nothing will link the legal operations
of the Moravianos to the Valtrovis.

68
00:06:47,615 --> 00:06:50,118
Only Mikoy can provide that.

69
00:06:52,411 --> 00:06:55,206
But how are we going to do that?
Mikoy isn’t here!

70
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:59,460
We can’t talk to him!
We can’t reach him! Okay?

71
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:03,214
Because all his calls are monitored 24/7.

72
00:07:03,297 --> 00:07:04,257
We can’t visit him.

73
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:06,384
So, what do you want to happen now, Bok?

74
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:08,261
Huh?

75
00:07:08,886 --> 00:07:10,638
Are we just going to wait
for his call forever?

76
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:24,610
Who is this?

77
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:27,363
Hello? Yes? It's Piolo Pascual.

78
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:30,867
If you're offering a loan again,
I’m not in the mood.

79
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,371
Mikoy?

80
00:07:35,455 --> 00:07:36,330
Yeah!

81
00:07:36,414 --> 00:07:37,957
Yeah, it’s really Mikoy!

82
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:39,375
<i>Come on.</i>

83
00:07:39,459 --> 00:07:41,210
<i>No "How are you" or anything?</i>

84
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:42,420
<i>"Are you okay?"</i>

85
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:44,505
I already know you’ve been missing me.

86
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:46,924
Silly!

87
00:07:47,758 --> 00:07:49,635
Things are chaotic here.

88
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,012
Show yourself already!

89
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:54,891
Here I am! That’s why I’m calling!

90
00:07:55,808 --> 00:07:57,435
Because I need to see you soon.

91
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:01,481
<i>Tomorrow, okay?</i>

92
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:14,494
Didn’t they even realize

93
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:17,538
that your brother Mikoy
is in a very dangerous situation?

94
00:08:17,622 --> 00:08:21,375
He has no idea how chaotic
and dangerous this world is.

95
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:24,504
He entered a relationship
with a criminal’s child.

96
00:08:24,587 --> 00:08:27,048
Chiara might even be a criminal, too!

97
00:08:27,131 --> 00:08:28,382
Hey! First of all,

98
00:08:29,967 --> 00:08:32,053
if there’s anyone I trust the most,

99
00:08:32,762 --> 00:08:33,763
it’s my brother Mikoy.

100
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:35,640
Fine.

101
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:38,809
If you’re right that he got
into a complicated

102
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,228
and dangerous situation,

103
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:43,648
I still believe
he’ll always do what’s right.

104
00:08:45,149 --> 00:08:48,361
Second, the way you talk, it’s like

105
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:50,905
you’re absolutely sure
the Valtrovis are evil.

106
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:54,617
I’m not even sure if everything
you told me is true.

107
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,118
Tell me.

108
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:58,788
Why shouldn’t I shoot you?

109
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:01,958
Will you join my enemies

110
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:04,502
who is now making a move against me?

111
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:08,506
You still haven’t changed, Norberto.

112
00:09:16,722 --> 00:09:18,766
I still know where you hide your gun.

113
00:09:23,479 --> 00:09:24,730
I knew it.

114
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:27,692
It felt a bit light.

115
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:33,114
Norberto, I didn’t come here to fight.

116
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:35,032
I’m here because I want to ask

117
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:38,494
what my child
has to do with the Valtrovis.

118
00:09:42,623 --> 00:09:46,419
You sound completely convinced
the Valtrovis are really bad.

119
00:09:46,502 --> 00:09:48,671
As if that’s already the truth?

120
00:09:48,754 --> 00:09:51,090
Because what? Your father said so?

121
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:53,301
Isn’t it possible
that your father is wrong?

122
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:56,846
Then you immediately judged
an entire family just like that?

123
00:09:59,307 --> 00:10:01,058
That’s the problem with you!

124
00:10:01,142 --> 00:10:03,894
The truth is already slapping you,
but you still refuse to face it!

125
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:06,731
Well, maybe it’s because

126
00:10:06,814 --> 00:10:10,067
you’re also enjoying the privileges
brought by the syndicates.

127
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,113
A foul is a foul!

128
00:10:14,196 --> 00:10:16,198
But if you’re going
to keep turning a blind eye,

129
00:10:16,282 --> 00:10:18,284
then don’t blame me

130
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:20,536
when something bad
happens again to your brother.

131
00:10:56,197 --> 00:10:57,740
That’s not funny!

132
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:00,076
It's just a joke.

133
00:11:02,536 --> 00:11:03,829
I’m sorry.

134
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:07,458
Oh no.

135
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:10,503
My sweetheart is in a bad mood, huh?

136
00:11:13,964 --> 00:11:15,591
Did I do something wrong?

137
00:11:21,597 --> 00:11:24,100
I’m doing everything you want, aren’t I?

138
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:25,935
I’m eating healthy foods.

139
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:28,187
I even eat bitter gourd.

140
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:30,272
And your dance therapy, too.

141
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:33,901
I’m even getting back
to my original stretchability.

142
00:11:34,985 --> 00:11:35,903
Look.

143
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:48,082
I’m okay now, sweetheart.

144
00:11:48,165 --> 00:11:49,500
You’re really good.

145
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:59,635
But I still need your help.

146
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:03,431
I was about to take a shower.

147
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:08,477
But I can’t reach…

148
00:12:09,562 --> 00:12:10,938
my back.

149
00:12:14,775 --> 00:12:16,819
There’s no wound there.

150
00:12:17,486 --> 00:12:19,113
On the other side.

151
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:27,329
And also, didn’t you say you’re okay now?

152
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:32,209
So you should be able to wash
any part of your body,

153
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:35,337
even your hard-to-reach areas,
without my help!

154
00:12:38,132 --> 00:12:39,717
I’m meeting my mom

155
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:43,262
for some "me" time.

156
00:12:43,345 --> 00:12:44,680
Huh?

157
00:12:48,851 --> 00:12:51,228
Why is she like that? What happened?

158
00:12:51,312 --> 00:12:53,481
- What did you do again?
- Nothing!

159
00:12:54,064 --> 00:12:57,568
I’m just my usual charming and cute self.

160
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:02,323
I used my Enrique Gil moves,
but still, no effect.

161
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:05,034
Maybe you did something not so good, dear.

162
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:07,703
Me? No way!

163
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,288
Me, Mom?

164
00:13:09,371 --> 00:13:11,207
I’m so good!

165
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,334
I follow all her instructions.

166
00:13:18,839 --> 00:13:20,758
Since I left the service,

167
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,010
I changed my name.

168
00:13:23,844 --> 00:13:26,180
Now I am Mario Pinagpala.

169
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:29,308
No matter what name you use,

170
00:13:30,142 --> 00:13:34,438
you are still known as Isidro Catacutan,

171
00:13:34,522 --> 00:13:38,359
the feared Butcher of Butuan.

172
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:41,862
That’s right.

173
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:45,157
And there’s still fear inside me.

174
00:13:47,076 --> 00:13:49,411
That’s why I need to know

175
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:52,748
what the truth really is
about the Valtrovi family.

176
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:54,833
Are they part

177
00:13:56,001 --> 00:13:57,670
of a big syndicate?

178
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:05,386
Let me ask you something.

179
00:14:06,053 --> 00:14:08,889
Did you thank her already?

180
00:14:12,851 --> 00:14:15,896
That’s exactly what I’m saying!

181
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,732
Huh! That’s what’s wrong with you.

182
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:21,193
You just keep tugging!

183
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:25,573
Do you even know
what she did for you? Huh?

184
00:14:25,656 --> 00:14:29,118
Since you’re in the hospital,
she hasn’t slept at all.

185
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:31,245
Just to watch over you.

186
00:14:32,204 --> 00:14:38,043
Every minute of her life,
she devoted to you!

187
00:14:38,127 --> 00:14:40,754
Just so you could recover immediately.

188
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:44,842
And then, not even a thank you.
You didn’t even say anything?

189
00:14:48,429 --> 00:14:50,514
Hey, Mikoy!

190
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:52,641
You should be ashamed, huh!

191
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:58,105
You need to repay her love
for what he showed you.

192
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,401
You need to reach the moon
and all the stars

193
00:15:02,484 --> 00:15:05,321
and offer them to her, huh?

194
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:10,200
So you can at least show her
that you appreciate her care.

195
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:11,160
That’s how it should be.

196
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:12,870
Roger that, Mom!

197
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:16,874
Operation "reach the stars
and the moon" commences.

198
00:15:16,957 --> 00:15:18,167
Good job, dear!

199
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:20,002
- Good job!
- Thank you, Mom.

200
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:22,546
Wait, wait. Where’s Dad?

201
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:24,131
Oh, I don’t know!

202
00:15:24,214 --> 00:15:26,425
He said he was visiting a friend.

203
00:15:27,217 --> 00:15:28,302
A friend?

204
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:32,556
Since when did Dad
have a friend here in Manila?

205
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:54,745
I didn’t know that this
was connected to a big syndicate.

206
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:03,963
It was just a desperate
kidnap for ransom group

207
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:06,215
that expected a big payday,

208
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:09,009
the ones who targeted the Valtrovis.

209
00:16:10,844 --> 00:16:13,097
Did you forget that I can read you easily?

210
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:17,267
I can tell when
you’re not telling the truth.

211
00:16:18,978 --> 00:16:21,271
I admire your instincts,

212
00:16:21,855 --> 00:16:23,732
but you are wrong in this case.

213
00:16:24,483 --> 00:16:26,318
I have never been wrong about you.

214
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,700
You don’t know me that well.

215
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:46,839
And what if I tell you
that my reliable source is…

216
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,049
your daughter Sofie.

217
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:56,974
- My own child told you that?
- Yes.

218
00:16:57,766 --> 00:16:59,184
I was actually surprised

219
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:03,605
that she shared this information
with my other child, Angelito.

220
00:17:04,481 --> 00:17:06,275
How did she meet Angelito?

221
00:17:07,443 --> 00:17:09,903
Actually, I don’t know.
But from what I understand,

222
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:13,991
they’re schoolmates,
and they’re in some kind of a…

223
00:17:15,075 --> 00:17:16,160
relationship.

224
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:20,622
What kind of relationship?

225
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:24,126
Kids these days, they call it,

226
00:17:24,626 --> 00:17:25,461
FUBU.

227
00:17:27,963 --> 00:17:28,797
FUBU?

228
00:17:30,924 --> 00:17:34,553
Your daughter's relationship status
is not my concern.

229
00:17:34,636 --> 00:17:36,096
What matters to me right now

230
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:38,640
is Mikoy and whether he’s safe.

231
00:17:39,516 --> 00:17:40,726
Actually, Norberto,

232
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:44,021
at first, I didn’t know anything,
I had no suspicions.

233
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:47,232
When Chiara and the Valtrovi family
came to us,

234
00:17:47,316 --> 00:17:49,735
when we received a large order

235
00:17:50,611 --> 00:17:53,280
and it was delivered to your office,

236
00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:58,952
But I still didn’t notice those red flags.

237
00:17:59,036 --> 00:18:01,914
And my child almost lost his life
because of this.

238
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:08,921
<i>There is no greater horror</i>

239
00:18:09,004 --> 00:18:11,840
<i>than seeing your child</i>
<i>fighting for their life.</i>

240
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:14,927
<i>That’s why I thought,</i>
<i>I knew I had to ask questions.</i>

241
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:20,516
I have a strong feeling that there’s…

242
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:26,271
there’s a bigger story
behind Mikoy being shot.

243
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:30,192
And it was your daughter
who confirmed my suspicions.

244
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:54,174
Mom?

245
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,221
Chiara?

246
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:03,225
Are you here?

247
00:19:28,125 --> 00:19:31,128
- Ah!
- Hey! Ouch! Ouch!

248
00:19:31,211 --> 00:19:33,922
Why are you hurting me, dear?

249
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:40,846
What are you imagining?

250
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:42,764
Ah!

251
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:45,475
Is it about what La Morte Bianca
wants you to do?

252
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:46,852
Mom!

253
00:19:51,815 --> 00:19:52,983
Alright.

254
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:56,111
Let’s just name her Bianca Umali?

255
00:19:57,613 --> 00:19:58,447
Mom!

256
00:19:58,530 --> 00:19:59,865
Bianca King?

257
00:20:00,449 --> 00:20:01,325
Mom!

258
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:06,079
I’m just trying to lighten
the mood because

259
00:20:06,163 --> 00:20:08,248
this family has been under so much stress.

260
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:09,833
It’s really overwhelming.

261
00:20:10,584 --> 00:20:13,212
Your Dad, he’s extremely stressed

262
00:20:13,795 --> 00:20:16,173
because he was given an ultimatum

263
00:20:16,256 --> 00:20:19,176
that we should have no more
enemies here in the Philippines.

264
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,595
And you, I know that

265
00:20:21,678 --> 00:20:24,514
you’re stressed too
because of your mission, right?

266
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:35,067
The truth is,

267
00:20:35,734 --> 00:20:38,278
I don’t know the answer to that question.

268
00:20:38,362 --> 00:20:41,740
You know that even if I know something,

269
00:20:42,783 --> 00:20:47,371
I cannot divulge that information
to a civilian like you.

270
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:48,497
Norberto!

271
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:53,710
If you were in my position,
and it was Sofie who was in danger…

272
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,466
If I were in your position,

273
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:01,927
I would do the same.

274
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:28,412
Idiot!

275
00:21:29,579 --> 00:21:30,539
Wait, Isidro.

276
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,416
Isidro, listen to me!

277
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:38,505
Am I doing the right thing?

278
00:21:39,506 --> 00:21:42,384
Why are you suddenly having doubts?

279
00:21:43,135 --> 00:21:44,845
What are you thinking about?

280
00:21:59,985 --> 00:22:02,988
And then after what he did for me,

281
00:22:03,071 --> 00:22:05,907
sacrificing himself for me,

282
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,909
I knew right there and then

283
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:10,412
that he’s the one
I want to be with for life.

284
00:22:11,246 --> 00:22:13,248
Oh? Well, there you go!

285
00:22:13,332 --> 00:22:14,416
So what’s the problem?

286
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:22,758
Of course not, dear.

287
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:26,887
You can see we’re having a serious
heart-to-heart talk,

288
00:22:26,970 --> 00:22:28,680
why would I laugh?
What kind of mother would I be

289
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:31,224
to laugh at your feelings
and turn them into a joke?

290
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:34,603
Okay.

291
00:22:34,686 --> 00:22:35,937
Well,

292
00:22:39,149 --> 00:22:40,442
I’m just thinking.

293
00:22:41,610 --> 00:22:43,904
What if Mikoy has flaws?

294
00:22:51,536 --> 00:22:53,038
he’s actually a womanizer?

295
00:22:57,876 --> 00:22:58,710
Mom!

296
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:01,088
You said you wouldn’t laugh!

297
00:23:01,171 --> 00:23:03,715
- What kind of mother are you?
- Sorry!

298
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:08,053
That Mikoy? Doing multiple
extra-curricular activities?

299
00:23:08,136 --> 00:23:10,180
- I don’t think so.
- Well,

300
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:13,850
he’s still a man. It’s not impossible.

301
00:23:14,351 --> 00:23:15,727
Well, you do have a point.

302
00:23:16,603 --> 00:23:19,731
But I don’t see Mikoy as someone

303
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:21,942
who can multi-task like that.

304
00:23:26,404 --> 00:23:28,698
Isidro, wait! Listen to me!

305
00:23:28,782 --> 00:23:32,035
Isidro! For once, can you listen to me?

306
00:23:33,954 --> 00:23:36,456
I know what’s going through your mind.

307
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:39,584
And I’m warning you, as a former friend,

308
00:23:40,335 --> 00:23:43,922
do not take the law into your own hands.

309
00:23:44,005 --> 00:23:48,218
Don’t do something
you’ll regret in the end.

310
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:50,762
We’re talking about
my family here, Norberto!

311
00:23:51,513 --> 00:23:52,514
My family!

312
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:57,102
And if your family was put
in a dangerous situation,

313
00:23:58,895 --> 00:24:01,106
no law would be able to stop me.

314
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:06,820
If I have to kill again,

315
00:24:06,903 --> 00:24:08,155
for them,

316
00:24:10,073 --> 00:24:10,991
I will do it.

317
00:24:19,207 --> 00:24:20,750
Well, my child,

318
00:24:21,835 --> 00:24:24,462
I’ve had so many relationships.

319
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:28,466
I’ve practically beaten
the United Nations in numbers.

320
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:32,012
I already know how to read
and judge men like…

321
00:24:32,846 --> 00:24:34,389
a flirt.

322
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,068
Isidro.

323
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,988
This is not the right way.

324
00:24:57,287 --> 00:24:59,497
So many of our friends
should’ve still been alive!

325
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:04,002
If they weren’t mistreated
by the system you’re talking about!

326
00:25:08,840 --> 00:25:13,053
Fixing the system that disgraced them!

327
00:25:15,931 --> 00:25:17,307
What a waste, Norberto.

328
00:25:19,434 --> 00:25:21,186
It looks like you’ve been
consumed by the system too.

329
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:27,651
You were the one who turned your back!

330
00:25:28,235 --> 00:25:31,071
You were the one who abandoned us!

331
00:25:31,154 --> 00:25:33,114
Where were you when I needed you?

332
00:25:34,032 --> 00:25:37,702
You were the one who quit
fighting for what’s right!

333
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:42,540
Just like before.

334
00:25:44,668 --> 00:25:46,086
You can’t stop me.

335
00:25:48,046 --> 00:25:50,257
I will do everything I have to do.

336
00:25:51,549 --> 00:25:55,762
I won’t stop you, my friend,
but let me warn you.

337
00:25:55,845 --> 00:25:59,015
If you do that, there’s no turning back.

338
00:25:59,099 --> 00:26:01,059
I will become your enemy.

339
00:26:01,142 --> 00:26:03,895
I will stop you.

340
00:26:38,596 --> 00:26:39,597
Where’s Mikoy?

341
00:26:39,681 --> 00:26:43,643
Oh, he didn’t tell you?
He went to the office.

342
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:45,687
<i>That’s what you should</i>
<i>watch out for with Mikoy, okay?</i>

343
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:47,147
<i>If there’s missing time for you.</i>

344
00:26:49,524 --> 00:26:52,694
<i>Mr. Pinagpala is currently</i>
<i>on indefinite leave.</i>

345
00:26:55,196 --> 00:26:56,114
You?!

346
00:27:01,036 --> 00:27:02,454
You may leave.

